# Millings Method™ Core

Governance-first architecture for pre-execution control, signal admissibility, and structural integrity in intelligent systems.

---

## Overview

The Millings Method™ is a system integrity architecture that governs:

- how signal is admitted  
- how state is formed  
- how execution occurs  
- and how alignment with reality is preserved over time  

It addresses a foundational failure in modern systems:

> Systems do not fail at execution.  
> They fail at what they were allowed to treat as signal.

---

## Core Principle

A system can be:

- logically correct  
- internally consistent  
- properly governed  

…and still produce incorrect outcomes

👉 if the underlying signal and resulting state are mis-specified.

---

## Problem

Most modern architectures focus on:

- model accuracy  
- decision quality  
- execution control  

But they assume:

👉 the signal entering the system is already valid

When that assumption fails:

- signal becomes mis-specified  
- state forms incorrectly  
- execution stabilizes error  
- systems remain coherent—but wrong  

---

